headline: Rich baby boomers are the future of airline travel
summary: As America’s aging Baby Boomers start to crack open their nest eggs in retirement, there’s speculation that they will use the contents to take flight. In a research note, TD Cowen (TD) analysts suggest that older travelers will present the airline industry with “golden opportunities.”
